The Sedona-Oak Creek Governing Board voted today that students may return to in-person instruction beginning Monday, August 24th. We are very excited to see students again! However, we will also continue to offer virtual access to classroom instruction. Below, please find links to the form that must be completed for each student indicating whether you’ll be returning to campus or continuing with virtual instruction. post_text:
The mission of Resilient Arizona Crisis Counseling Program is to assist individuals and communities in recovering from the psychological effects of the Coronavirus pandemic through community-based outreach, emotional support and educational services.

Services are provided at no cost and are available to anyone who has been impacted by the pandemic. These services are provided in safe, accessible telephonic and virtual locations. Services can be provided in a group setting or one-on-one and include supportive crisis counseling, education, development of coping skills, and connection to appropriate resources.

https://resilientarizona.org/about

post_text:
The district's reopening plan was approved by the Board on July 7. Although our hope is to be able to resume in-person classes as soon as we are able, our Continuity of Operations Plan details three structures: 1. In-person learning; 2. Blended learning; and 3. Virtual learning.

In response to Governor Ducey's Executive Order, we will start school in Structure 3 (Virtual learning) on August 5 with the plan to move to Structure 1 (In-person learning) on August 17.

To prepare for our first day of school and kick off the new year, we will be hosting pre-registration days on July 27-29 at both campuses. (Details are coming!)

Last night's Commencement Ceremony video was AMAZING!

In case you missed it or want a copy of the video for yourself, a download link will be posted on http://www.sedona.k12.az.us/ at 11:00 a.m. today!

We want to give a HUGE shout-out to our graduates and to all of those who worked so hard to put this production together!

Nathaniel Wolkstein - Your violin performances of The National Anthem and Pomp & Circumstance were SPECTACULAR!

Christina Schweiss - Your last high school performance is literally one for the history books! FABULOUS!

Dylan Beattie & Christian Welch - Thanks for your willingness to capture your classmates' celebrations and accomplishments on film!

Jeremy Hawkes - You produced a memory better than we could have ever imagined! You are so very TALENTED!

A very special THANK YOU goes out to the Sedona Education Foundation and the Arizona Community Foundation! We couldn't have made this happen without your support!
💜💜💜

Sedona Red Rock Jr/Sr High School
April 22 at 5:50 PM ·

Scorpion Class of 2020: Commencement plans are underway, and we are so excited to honor and celebrate YOU! Given these unprecedented times and the need to ensure the health and safety of all involved, we are going to make the best of this situation! You will still hear the speeches, walk across the stage in cap & gown, and be recognized for your incredible accomplishments! All of this will be captured by a professional videographer to share with friends and family near and far!

Be sure to call Mrs. Edwards at 928-204-6720 to make an appointment for your commencement session. You will also need to bring with you:
* A short quote
* A photo of just you
* A photo of you with a classmate(s), if you have one
* Your vote for Student Choice Faculty Speaker

You and your classmates have made an impression on each of us, and now you're truly making your mark on history! Let's create a unique, amazing experience for you to look back on for years to come!

#ScorpionStrong

Sedona Red Rock Jr/Sr High School
April 9 at 11:56 AM ·

The 2020-2021 Arizona Governor's Youth Commission is seeking student leaders! Interested 10th, 11th, and 12th grade students are encouraged to apply!

Established in 1989, the Governor’s Youth Commission (GYC) is a diverse body of Arizona’s high school students composed of members from all across the state. The purpose of the GYC is to engage youth through innovative programs, events, and campaigns that effectively serve their communities in areas that are most meaningful to them and the Governor.

Issue Areas: Human Trafficking Prevention, Teen Dating Violence Prevention, Education, Substance Abuse Prevention, Distracted Driving Prevention

To Apply: https://goyff.az.gov/councils-commissions/governors-youth-commission

post_text:
Mr. Dearden sent a call to families this afternoon to provide an update on the things we're proud of during this unprecedented time:

* Our essential staff members who are coming in to work to meet students' needs every day: Secretaries, Transportation, Food Service, Custodians, and
Administrators.

* In 5 days (3/18 - 3/24), we have distributed 1,926 meals to children in the community.

* We have checked out over 70 Chromebooks.

* We have given away 75 iMac desktop computers to students.

* Teachers are providing consistent assignments, supporting students & families, and grading incoming work.

* Students are rising to the challenge of a new learning format and are communicating with teachers and completing their work.

We are so grateful for the outpouring of support from our parents and community partners. We miss seeing you all at school!

post_text: Congratulations to our Sedona Red Rock Mathletes for placing 9th out of 60 teams in the group question division and 5th out of 14 schools in the college speed round at the NAU Math Day Competition! An example question was “Find an ordered pair of positive integers (m,n) that satisfies the equation 1/m + 1/n + 1/mn = 1/5.” 🤔 The answer by the way is m = 10, n = 11. Tax Credit Contributions paid for Red Rock's participation in this event. If you would like to support future academic competitions like this, please select either Student Field Trips or Clubs when you complete your 2019 Sedona Kids Tax Credit Contribution. http://www.sedonak12.org/SedonaKidsTaxCredit.aspx

post_text:
Hello Sedona Red Rock Jr-Sr High Families and Community,

We would like to thank the Sedona Police Department for their partnership in prioritizing student safety on our campus. The police department initiated a lockdown today. A vehicle on campus raised concern with our student resource officer who initiated the lockdown until the owner of that vehicle could be located. All areas of campus were searched and cleared by police officers. The owner of that vehicle, the person of concern, was located off campus. The vehicle had been driven to campus by another person.

We are grateful to have law enforcement partners, particularly our SRO on campus, as safety is our highest priority. Thank you for your support, confidence, and patience as well as we verified student safety before releasing students to their next classes.

SOCUSD Communications, Jennifer Chilton 928-204-6828 chilton@sedonak12.org

post_text:
Dear Sedona-Oak Creek Families,

We have been watching weather advisements and communicating with other area service agencies in determining whether Sedona-Oak Creek School District can safely transport your student to and from school tomorrow, Thursday, February 21, 2019.

In order to avoid any potential travel danger, either for buses or for families individually transporting children to school, we have decided to close all district schools Thursday. After-school activities, practices, and athletic events are also cancelled.

We will continue to closely monitor weather conditions tomorrow in order to make a decision regarding the district status for Friday.

Thank you for your patience and support in prioritizing student safety.

Sedona Dot Biz
January 8, 2019 at 10:30 AM ·

January 9th and 10th, Sedona Fire District will be hosting Active Shooter Hostile Emergency Response (ASHER) training. More than 70 attendees will participate in the training which will be held at Sedona Fire District Station 1 and Big Park School. This training is for first responders who may be called upon to deal with these types of incidents. “No one likes to consider the possibility that these events could potentially occur in our communities,” said Michael Duran, Sedona Fire District Training Officer, “but we must prepare for them, nonetheless.”
Read more→ http://www.sedona.biz/news-from-sedona/sedona-fire-department-news-from-sedona/sedona-fire-district-to-host-active-shooter-training/
